== 外部連結及參考 ==
* [https://web.archive.org/web/20160217105359/http://www.inference.phy.cam.ac.uk/mackay/itila/book.html On-line textbook: Information Theory, Inference, and Learning Algorithms], by David MacKay, has many chapters on Bayesian methods, including introductory examples; arguments in favour of Bayesian methods (in the style of [[Edwin_Thompson_Jaynes|Edwin Jaynes]]); state-of-the-art [[Monte_Carlo_method|Monte Carlo method]]s, [[message-passing_method|message-passing method]]s, and [[Calculus_of_variations|variational methods]]; and examples illustrating the intimate connections between Bayesian inference and [[data_compression|data compression]].
* [http://www.dcs.qmw.ac.uk/%7Enorman/BBNs/BBNs.htm A nice on-line introductory tutorial to Bayesian probability] {{Wayback|url=http://www.dcs.qmw.ac.uk/%7Enorman/BBNs/BBNs.htm |date=20090504220301 }} from Queen Mary University of London
* Jaynes, E.T. (1998) [http://www-biba.inrialpes.fr/Jaynes/prob.html ''Probability Theory : The Logic of Science''] {{Wayback|url=http://www-biba.inrialpes.fr/Jaynes/prob.html |date=20201108171426 }}.
* Bretthorst, G. Larry, 1988, [http://bayes.wustl.edu/glb/book.pdf ''Bayesian Spectrum Analysis and Parameter Estimation'']{{Wayback|url=http://bayes.wustl.edu/glb/book.pdf |date=20110514121949 }} in Lecture Notes in Statistics, 48, Springer-Verlag, New York, New York;
* http://www-groups.dcs.st-andrews.ac.uk/history/Mathematicians/Ramsey.html {{Wayback|url=http://www-groups.dcs.st-andrews.ac.uk/history/Mathematicians/Ramsey.html |date=20190609234053 }}
* David Howie: ''Interpreting Probability, Controversies and Developments in the  Early Twentieth Century'', Cambridge University Press, 2002, ISBN 0-521-81251-8
* Colin Howson and Peter Urbach: ''Scientific Reasoning: The Bayesian Approach'', Open Court Publishing, 2nd edition, 1993, ISBN 0-8126-9235-7, focuses on the philosophical underpinnings of Bayesian and frequentist statistics.  Argues for the subjective interpretation of probability.
* Wing-Ho Shum, Kwong-Sak Leung, and Man-Leung Wong. Learning functional dependency networks based on genetic programming. In ICDM05, Proceedings of IEEE International Conference on Data Mining, pages 232-230, 2005.
* Luc Bovens and Stephan Hartmann: ''Bayesian Epistemology''. Oxford: Oxford University Press 2003. Extends the Bayesian program to more complex decision scenarios (e.g. dependent and partially reliable witnesses and measurement instruments) using Bayesian Network models. The book also proofs an impossibility theorem for coherence orderings over information sets and offers a measure that induces a partial coherence ordering.
* Jeff Miller [https://web.archive.org/web/19991001182725/http://members.aol.com/jeff570/b.html "Earliest Known Uses of Some of the Words of Mathematics (B)"]
* James Franklin [http://www.press.jhu.edu/books/title_pages/2844.html The Science of Conjecture: Evidence and Probability Before Pascal]{{Wayback|url=http://www.press.jhu.edu/books/title_pages/2844.html |date=20080207144237 }}, history from a Bayesian point of view.
* Paul Graham [http://www.paulgraham.com/better.html "Bayesian spam filtering"]{{Wayback|url=http://www.paulgraham.com/better.html |date=20100621011536 }} 
* novomind AG [https://web.archive.org/web/20061205061705/http://imaillight.com/ "Outlook categorizing tool based on Bayesian filtering"]
* Howard Raiffa ''Decision Analysis: Introductory Lectures on Choices under Uncertainty''. McGraw Hill, College Custom Series. (1997) ISBN 0-07-052579-X
* Devender Sivia, ''Data Analysis: A Bayesian Tutorial''. Oxford: Clarendon Press (1996), pp. 7-8. ISBN 0-19-851889-7
* Henk Tijms: ''Understanding Probability'', Cambridge University Press, 2004
* Is the portrait of Thomas Bayes authentic? [http://www.york.ac.uk/depts/maths/histstat/bayespic.htm Who Is this gentleman? When and where was he born?]{{Wayback|url=http://www.york.ac.uk/depts/maths/histstat/bayespic.htm |date=20171021215946 }} ''The IMS Bulletin'', Vol. '''17''' (1988), No. 3, pp. 276-278
